          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-132-904A-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-132-904A-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-132-904A-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-1" n="1">The Rod was but a harmless Wand,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-2" n="2">While Moses held it in his Hand,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-3" n="3">But soon as e'er he laid it down,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-4" n="4">'Twas a devouring Serpent grown.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-5" n="5"><lb/>Our great Magician Hamet Sid,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-6" n="6">Reverses what y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Prophet did;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-7" n="7">His Rod was honest English Wood,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-8" n="8">That senceless in a Corner stood,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-9" n="9">Till Metamorphos'd by his Grasp,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-10" n="10">It grew an all-devouring Asp,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-11" n="11">Would hiss, &amp; sting, &amp; roll, &amp; Twist,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-12" n="12">By y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> meer Virtue of his Fist:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-13" n="13">But when he laid it down, as quick</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-14" n="14">Resum'd y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Figure of a Stick.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-15" n="15"><lb/>So to Her Midnight Feasts y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Hag,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-16" n="16">Rides on a Broomstick for a Nag,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-17" n="17">That, rais'd by Magick of her Breech,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-18" n="18">O'er Sea &amp; Land convys y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Witch;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-19" n="19">But with y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Morning-Dawn resumes</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-20" n="20">The Peacefull State of Comon Brooms.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-21" n="21"><lb/>They tell us something strange &amp; odd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-22" n="22">About a certain Magick Rod,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-23" n="23">That, bending down it's Top, divines</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-24" n="24">When e'er y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Soil has Golden Mines:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-25" n="25">Where there are none, it stands erect,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-26" n="26">Scorning to show y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> least Respect.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-27" n="27">As ready was y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Wand of Sid</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-28" n="28">To bend where Golden Mines were hid;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-29" n="29">In Scottish Hills found precious Ore,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-30" n="30">Where none e'er look'd for it before;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-31" n="31">And by a gentle Bow, divin'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-32" n="32">How well a Cully's Purse was lin'd:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-33" n="33">To a forlorn &amp; broken Rake,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-34" n="34">Stood w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi>out Motion like a Stake.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-35" n="35"><lb/>The Rod of Hermes was renown'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-36" n="36">For Charmes above &amp; under Ground;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-37" n="37">To sleep could Mortal Eye-lids fix</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-38" n="38">And drive departed Souls to Styx.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-39" n="39">That Rod was Iust a Type of Sid's,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-40" n="40">Which o're a British Senate's Lids,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-41" n="41">Could scatter Opium full as well,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-42" n="42">And drive as many Souls to Hell.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-43" n="43"><lb/>Sid's Rod was Slender, White &amp; Tall,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-44" n="44">Which oft he us'd to fish withall</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-45" n="45">A Place was fastned to y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Hook,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-46" n="46">And many score of Gudgeons took;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-47" n="47">Yet still so happy was his Fate,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-48" n="48">He caught his Fish &amp; sav'd his Bait.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-49" n="49"><lb/>Sid's Brethren of y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Conj'ring Tribe</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-50" n="50">A Circle w<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> their Rod describe,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-51" n="51">Which proves a Magical Redoubt</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-52" n="52">To keep mischievous Spirits out:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-53" n="53">Sid's Rod was of a larger Stride</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-54" n="54">And made a Circle thrice as wide,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-55" n="55">Where Spirits throng'd w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> hideous Din,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-56" n="56">And he stood there to take them in.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-57" n="57">But when y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> enchanted Rod was broke,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-58" n="58">The vanish'd in a stinking Smoak.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-59" n="59"><lb/>Achilles's Scepter was of Wood,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-60" n="60">Like Sid's, but nothing near so Good,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-61" n="61">Tho' down from Ancestors Divine</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-62" n="62">Trnsmitted to y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Heroes Line,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-63" n="63">Thence thro' a long Descent of Kings,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-64" n="64">Came an Heir-loom, as Homer sings,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-65" n="65">Tho' this Description looks so big,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-66" n="66">That Scepter was a sapless Twig:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-67" n="67">Which from y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> fatall Day when first</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-68" n="68">It left y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Forest where 'twas Nurst,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-69" n="69">As Homer tells us us o'er &amp; o'er,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-70" n="70">Nor Leaf, nor Fruit, nor Blossom bore.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-71" n="71">Sid's Scepter, full of Iuice, did shoot</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-72" n="72">In Golden Boughs, &amp; Golden Fruit,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-73" n="73">And He, y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Dragon never sleeping,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-74" n="74">Guarded each fair Hesperian Pippin.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-75" n="75">No Hobby-Horse, w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> gorgeous Top,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-76" n="76">The dearest in Charles Mather's Shop,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-77" n="77">Or glitt'ring Tinsell of May-Fair,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-78" n="78">Could w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> this Rod of Sid compare.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-79" n="79"><lb/>Dread S<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>, then why wer't thou so mad</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-80" n="80">To break thy Rod like naughty Lad?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-81" n="81">You should have kist it in yo<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> Distress,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-82" n="82">And then return'd it to yo<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> Mistress,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-83" n="83">Or made it a Newmarket Switch,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-84" n="84">And not a Rod for thy own Breech.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-85" n="85">For since old Sid has broken this,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-132-904A-line-86" n="86">His next will be a Rod in Piss.</l>
          </lg>
